comment: LATR shows that Thompson (GSW) and Green (GSW) maintain legal guarding positions as they contest Westbrook's (OKC) driving layup attempt.
Adams (OKC) and Barnes (GSW) make incidental contact when they engage for the rebound.
RATR shows that Adams (OKC) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Green's (GSW) non-shooting arm that does not affect his driving layup attempt.
Thompson (GSW) maintains a legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Westbrook (OKC) that does not affect his RSBQ.
RATR shows that Green (GSW) jumps from point A to point B and makes body contact with Adams (OKC) that affects his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Iguodala (GSW) sets the screen on Waiters (OKC) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
RHH shows that Adams (OKC) and Ibaka (OKC) maintain legal guarding positions as they defend Thompson's (GSW) drive to the basket and layup attempt.
Ibaka (OKC) and Green (GSW) make incidental contact with one another during rebounding.
[Incidental or immaterial] Green (GSW) is in the paint without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.
Roberson (OKC) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Iguodala (GSW) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Thompson (GSW) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Westbrook (OKC) that does not affect his RSBQ.
Westbrook (OKC) turns toward the referee to request a timeout as he slides his pivot foot. The referee is focused on a possible take foul or timeout and misses the travel violation.
Iguodala (GSW) commits a take foul on Westbrook (OKC).
Westbrook (OKC) enters the lane prior to the ball touching the rim. The clock is reset after the violation is called.
Barnes (GSW) and Durant (OKC) briefly engage and separate during rebounding.
Thompson (GSW) commits a take foul on Westbrook (OKC).
Iguodala (GSW) sets the screen on Waiters (OKC) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Curry (GSW) gathers the ball on his left foot, establishing his pivot foot. He then lifts it and steps before his field goal attempt.
